    <briefdescription>
<para>Exception type raised by the Tryll C++ client library. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>All failures surfaced by <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_tryll_client" kindref="compound">Tryll::Client::TryllClient</ref> and <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_agent_proxy" kindref="compound">Tryll::Client::AgentProxy</ref> — server-reported errors, protocol decode failures, and connection-level problems — are raised as <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_tryll_error" kindref="compound">Tryll::Client::TryllError</ref>. Server-reported errors carry a numeric code that matches the ranges defined in <computeroutput>server/common/include/tryll/ErrorCodes.h</computeroutput>; client-side errors (timeouts, closed socket) carry code 0. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
